---
import Docs from "../../layouts/Docs.astro";
import { snippet } from "../../lib/snippets";
---
<Docs title="Sessions" description="Auto-save and resume conversations across sessions.">
  <h1>Sessions</h1>

  <h2>Auto-Save</h2>
  <p>
    Sessions auto-save on exit. The full conversation history, memory state, and context are
    preserved. Resume exactly where you left off.
  </p>

  <h2>Resume</h2>
  <pre><code># Resume the most recent session
{snippet("cli.resume")}

# Resume a specific session (prefix match)
{snippet("cli.resume_specific")}

# List saved sessions
{snippet("slash.sessions")}</code></pre>

  <h2>Session Contents</h2>
  <p>A saved session includes:</p>
  <ul>
    <li>Full conversation history (all segments with metadata)</li>
    <li>Model and provider state at time of save</li>
    <li>Working memory pins</li>
    <li>Active persona and tone</li>
    <li>Turn count, tool call count, session duration</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>Disable Auto-Save</h2>
  <pre><code>{snippet("cli.no_session")}</code></pre>
  <p>
    Disables session auto-save for this run. Useful for one-off queries or sensitive work
    you don't want persisted to disk.
  </p>

  <h2>Headless Mode</h2>
  <p>
    For scripted/CI use, pass a prompt directly:
  </p>
  <pre><code># Execute a single prompt and exit
{snippet("cli.headless_prompt")}

# Read prompt from a file
{snippet("cli.headless_file")}

# Limit turns
{snippet("cli.headless_bounded")}</code></pre>

  <h2>Smoke Tests</h2>
  <pre><code>{snippet("cli.smoke")}</code></pre>
  <p>
    Runs 4 headless smoke tests through the LLM bridge: basic response, bash tool use,
    file read, and arithmetic validation. Useful for verifying provider connectivity and
    basic agent functionality after updates. 60-second timeout per test.
  </p>
</Docs>
